{
  "texts": [
    "Active learning has been utilized to minimize the effort of expensive human experts in labeling plankton image data (Luo et al. 2005; Li et al. 2021a).",
    "The basic idea behind active learning is to select only the most informative samples for labeling.",
    "A classifier is first trained on a small initial training set and the method iteratively seeks to find the most informative samples from an unlabeled dataset.",
    "These samples are then labeled by a human expert and the model is re-trained.",
    "A simple active learning technique for plankton images called \"breaking ties\" was proposed by Luo et al. (2005)."
  ]
}